<Author>JCTravel13
<Content>The worst hotel I have ever encountered Without doubt this is the worst hotel I have ever stayed in.I travelled with my wife who was a delegate at a conference. We paid extra for a larger room with more facilities. What these 'extra' facilities were we could not tell.The room was clean but very bare and only furnished with very basic cheap furnitureFirst thing I noticed - NO ROOM SAFE - nowhere to keep a laptop or other valuables. The reception staff said we could keep valuables in the reception safe - just imagine 1000 delegates all trying to keep their laptops in one safe. In addition the hotel specifically stated that no resposibility would be taken for any valuables not in the hotel safe.The beds were adequate but the pillows were paper-thin - I needed three which were equal to one normal pillow.The towels were so thin and worn - a bit like trying to dry yourself on tissue paper.There were no normal toiletries - shampoo/conditioner /bar of soap. etc. even water for taking tablets had to be paid for at expensive minibar pricesThe sink plug did not retain water because it did not fit.The shower head was broken and hanging loose.There is no facility in the room to make a cup of tea or coffee - and there is no room service.There are no spa or swimming facilities.Food and drink are extremely expensive (the bar prices doubled during the period of the conference)At checkout they tried to charge us for using PayTV and argued with us to the point of shouting - quite disgraceful behaviour. They claimed that everybody tries to pretend that PayTV was not used.  I know that it was not used at any time we were in the room - perhaps the management need to investigate their staff or their PayTV software. The location of the hotel is in a very undesirable area - you would not dream of going for a walkabout at night or even during the day. Security was nonexistent - anybody could enter the building and go anywhere to any floor in the hotel.The conference organisers had described this hotel as being an award winning hotel - somebody must be joking!  Anyone thinking of staying at this hotel I would recommend to reconsider - there are far better and cheaper hotels in the centre of Berlin. e.g. 'The Swissotol' in the centre which is excellent in every way I hope this review may help anyone to avoid the experiences we encountered. 
<Date>Nov 9, 2008
