<Author>MissJasmine
<Content>We felt royally ripped off.Never Never again would we stay here We stayed at the Estrel because we were attending a trade show in Berlin and this hotel was recommended by the organisers of the show. As we wanted some extra nights in Berlin, We arrived 2 days before the trade show started. This was a real eye opener. In the days before the main trade show guests arrived, a beer was priced reasonably at 3 Euro. However on the Wednesday night all the bar prices leaped up by more than 100% pricing a beer now at 6 Euro and a GT at a staggering 10.50 Euro. Combined with this the service was very slow and the staff on times quite surly. Other problems included extra items added to bar bills and people being charged for drinks they never even had. There are several restaurants at the hotel and we ate in most of them. The service here was a little better but the food was really overpriced, just like the drinks. The food itself was OK but nothing special. We were very disappointed with this hotel and would not choose to stay there again. We felt royally ripped off. 
