<Author>Esporta
<Content>Adequate for a good sleep We stayed her ewhilst travelling on an Archers/Cosmos Eastern European tour in June 2008. As I did not know the actual cost of a room I could not assign value for money because expected quality must be related to price. This hotel was perfectly adequate for a good quiet night鈥檚 sleep in a large air- conditioned room with comfortable big beds and good bathroom facilities. The breakfast was excellent and in comfortable surroundings with items restocked by friendly staff. As a general comment regarding all our 9 hotels, the pillows were always so thin, or were so soft they ended up thin, that we always requested extras. They were delivered promptly at the Estrel. After long journey we were disappointed to see there was no tea making facilities in the room (this was the same in 8 out of the 9 hotels we used).Considering the hotel was massive I was surprised that it did not have a large gym and swimming pool. The isolated position of the hotel outside town means you do not have convenient access to the city for a stroll or to sample the nightlife in the evenings. This was not quite so important for older people, like myself, who only stopped 2 nights after tiring days of sightseeing. However, I would not stay here for a longer holiday. We did travel back to the hotel on the U-Bahn on one day and found it quite easy with one change required.I would not insult the locals by saying the area was seedy but it was not the sort of area you would choose for an after dinner stroll. We walked down to the local Lidl and did not find it at all intimidating. 
