<Content>Big but not great We stayed here one night before jumping on a train to Prague. The hotel is okay. The rooms are cheap looking Ikea decorated things. Trendy but cheap. The beds are not comfortable. They are thin and hard and the pillows are super thin; like putting a sheet under your head as a pillow. The bathrooms were clean and nice. Room was average and small as you would expect.Breakfast is above average with eggs, sausage, breads, cereals and more. Staff is okay, not overly friendly but not unfriendly. They are helpful in telling you how to get around town. It's a huge hotel so if you have a big group then it's a good place to stay. It's just around the corner from the Metro (about two short blocks) but it's in a slightly seedy area. We didn't have any problems even in the night walking around but it looks a bit scary. I think it's just very Berlin; the entire city looks a bit seedy. 
