<Content>Great Hotel My wife and I stayed in the Estrel Hotel in July 2007 for 4 days, the hotel itself is excellent, very modern, clean and has excellent facilities. Like most things in Germany everything runs like clockwork, the dining facilities were very nice and I would recommend this hotel to any traveller looking to visit Berlin. It is handy enough for Schonefeld Airport, (only one stop from Treptower Park), and is only a few stops from the city centre.The hotel is a short walk from the Sonnenallee U-Bahn station and although the local area looks a bit rough this will not effect your stay. (You take a right when you come out the station, walk about 100 yards and the Estrel is across the road to your right) 
