<Content>only for business While attending a 5 day conference, I spent two nights at the Estrel because I had to participate late in the evening or very early in the morning on two days. I was glad to be able to return to my usual accomodation in the city after two nights. The hotel itself is not bad; the rooms are bigger than average, clean and comfortable. I found the breakfast to be very good, and the personnel friendly. I found the restaurant area to be too noisy - it's more like a food court in a shopping center than three distinct restaurants, as they claim them to be. I abandoned my initial plan to invite a friend to their top-notch restaurant Sanssouci, as it does not look at all as classy as it seems on the web site. The biggest drawback of the hotel, however, is its location, as others have stated before. The hotel was chosen as a conference venue for its sheer size, as it was the only hotel in Berlin able to accomodate that many people. The hotel hosts a star look-alike show, which looks cheap judging from their advertisements, and gives an idea about the non-business public they try to attract. Definately not a 4 star hotel. 
