<Content>very disappointing hotel Overall I was very disappointed about the hotel. I was there for a global conference (Airline) so I was expecting to see at least some sense of global standards when it came to the hotel. Was I wrong, now I am not one to be petty, however, one would cetainly expect a hotel/conference center that claims to be the largest in Germany to have have a clock radio in the room, or a small coffee maker, individual ammenities for daily use instead of unitype orange colored hand/hair and body soap. The use of a iron and ironing board for more than 30 minutes whether you're done or not, it goes. Hotel restaurants that don't run out of food during lunch, The so called fitness center consisted of 1 treadmill, 1 stationary bike and 1 lifting machine and unless you're there at 0500 to workout, you can forget about using the equipment. This again is for a hotel that has 1,100 rooms.People posted the hotel was in the middle of no where and they were exactly right. Cab rides to/from the more active parts of the city were 19-24 euros and as much as the transit system was excellent, (I took it from Tegel to the hotel for 2e) spending a good amount of time on the train or bus is not what I would want to do again when visiting as I prefer walking. Could this be a very nice hotel, yes, but it has plenty of work to do to get there. 
